config ZMK_SETTING_EXPOSE
    bool "Expose Zephyr settings via ZMK Studio RPC"
    depends on ZMK_STUDIO
    depends on SETTINGS
    help
      Enables the setting_expose custom Studio RPC subsystem, which allows
      a connected ZMK Studio web UI to list, read, write, and delete Zephyr
      settings stored on the device.

      The subsystem requires the ZMK Studio unlock command (SECURED security
      level) to prevent unauthorized access to device settings.

if ZMK_SETTING_EXPOSE

config ZMK_SETTING_EXPOSE_UNIT_TEST
    bool "Run setting_expose RPC unit tests at boot (for testing only)"
    depends on LOG
    help
      When enabled, a SYS_INIT function exercises the setting_expose RPC
      handler at boot and logs PASS/FAIL results for each test case.
      This option is intended for automated testing only.

endif
